Serves 4Ingredients:4 chicken breast filletsOil, as needed1 onion, chopped5ml (1 tsp) cumin seeds5ml (1 tsp) ginger paste2 fresh red chillies, chopped10ml (2 tsp) concentrated tamarind pulp60ml ( cup) treacle brown sugar2.5ml ( tsp) salt5ml (1 tsp) chilli flakes2.5ml ( tsp) coarse pepper250ml (1 cup) coconut creamMethod:1) Preheat a griddle pan. Coat the fillets with oil and grill on both sides till cooked through and lightly browned. Remove and set aside. 2) Heat a drizzle of oil in a pan and fry the onion, cumin seeds, ginger paste and fresh chillies until onion is soft. Add tamarind, sugar, salt, chilli flakes and pepper and stir over gentle heat until sugar has dissolved. 3) Place chicken in the tamarind sauce and pour over the coconut cream. Stir to mix, simmer for 5 minutes and serve.